https://www.server-world.info/en/note?os=CentOS_6&p=x
 	
Desktop Environment is not neccessary for Server usage, though. But Sometimes installation or using an application requires Desktop Environment, then build Desktop Environment as follwos.
[1]	Install GNOME Desktop Environment on here.
[root@dlp ~]# sudo yum -y groupinstall "X Window System" 
[root@dlp ~]# sudo yum -y groupinstall "Desktop" 
[root@dlp ~]# sudo yum -y groupinstall "General Purpose Desktop"
[2]	Input a command like below after finishing installation of new packages.
[root@dlp ~]# startx
[3]	GNOME Desktop Environments starts like follows.
tigervnc-server

yum -y install tigervnc-server
yum -y groupinstall "X Window System"  "Desktop"  "General Purpose Desktop"
